{{Infobox company | name = Gerlach Barklow Co. | logo = | caption = | trading_name = <!-- d/b/a/, doing business as - if different from legal name above --> | native_name = <!-- Company's name in home country language --> | native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-2 code, e.g. "fr" for French. If there is more than one native name, in different languages, enter those names using {{tl|lang}}, instead. --> | romanized = | former type = | type = | traded_as = | industry = [[Calendar|Art calendar]] [[factory]] and [[Advertising agency|advertising company]] | genre = <!-- Only used with media and publishing companies --> | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = 1907 <!-- City, Country ({{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}}) --> | founder = | defunct = 1971<!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location_city = [[Joliet, Illinois]] | location_country = [[United States]] | locations = <!-- Number of locations, stores, offices &c. --> | area_served = | key_people = | products = | production = | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = <!-- Only used with financial services companies --> | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | footnotes = | intl = | bodystyle = }} The '''Gerlach Barklow Co.''' was an art [[calendar]] factory located in [[Joliet, Illinois]], which was "one of the largest calendar and [[Advertising agency|advertising companies]] in America."<ref>{{Cite web | title = Gerlach Barklow | work = Barlow Clearinghouse-Genealogy | accessdate = 2013-06-07 | year = 2007 | url = http://www.barlowgenealogy.com/Illinois/BGco.html }}</ref><ref name="arcadia">{{Cite web | title = Joliet's Gerlach Barklow Calendar Company - Historical Photos & Images of Joliet's Gerlach Barklow Calendar Company | work = Arcadia Publishing | accessdate = 2013-06-07 | url = http://www.arcadiapublishing.com/9780738577265/Joliet-s-Gerlach-Barklow-Calendar-Company }}</ref> the company was founded in 1907.<ref name="arcadia"/> The factory employed over 1,500 people at its peak in the 1950s.<ref>{{Cite news | last = Sorensen | first = Karen | title = Old Calendars Now Now Coveted by Collectors, Plainfield Historians Say | work = Plainfield Patch | location = Plainfield, IL | accessdate = 2013-06-07 | date = 2012-02-22 | url = http://plainfield.patch.com/groups/arts-and-entertainment/p/calendar-b4568dd4 }}</ref>
Artists who worked for Gerlach Barklow included [[Arthur H. Hider]], [[Bradshaw Crandell]], [[Adelaide Hiebel]],<ref>{{Cite web | title = Adelaide Hiebel | work = CityofJoliet.com | accessdate = 2013-06-07 | url = http://www.cityofjoliet.com/halloffame/artists/adelaidehiebel.htm }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | title = AdelaideHiebel.com - Home | accessdate = 2013-06-07 | url = http://adelaidehiebel.com/index.php }}</ref> and Zula Kenyon.<ref>{{Cite web | title = ZulaKenyon.com | accessdate = 2013-06-07 | url = http://zulakenyon.com/ }}</ref> Many of the company's artists were women, or local residents, and many local residents served as artists' models. [[Lois Delander]] of Joliet, better known as Miss America 1927, was among the most famous models. A Gerlach-Barklow fan is displayed in the collection of the [[Oakland Museum of California]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Gerlach-Barklow Company. Joliet, IL, advertisement, rigid fan |work=[[Oakland Museum of California]] |url=http://collections.museumca.org/?q=collection-item/200302 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130713030521/http://collections.museumca.org/?q=collection-item/200302 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2013-07-13 }}</ref>
Gerlach Barklow calendars were purchased by businesses to be given to their important customers as gifts.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Then & Now: Gerlach-Barklow Co. |work=Joliet Herald News |accessdate=2013-06-07 |date=2011-12-04 |url=http://heraldnews.suntimes.com/news/8553722-418/then-now-gerlach-barklow-co.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130705144637/http://heraldnews.suntimes.com/news/8553722-418/then-now-gerlach-barklow-co.html |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2013-07-05 }}</ref>
